### sb-version-sandbox — experiment walkthrough
### Use with the IntelliJ HTTP client or the VS Code "REST Client" extension.
@host = http://localhost:8080

############################################################
# 1. Basic CRUD via MongoRepository (normal versioned path)
############################################################

### List seeded products (each was inserted with version=0)
GET {{host}}/api/products

### Create a product -> note "version": 0 in the response
POST {{host}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Wireless Mouse",
  "category": "electronics",
  "price": 39.90,
  "stock": 40
}

### Grab an id from the list above, then fetch it
GET {{host}}/api/products/PUT_ID_HERE

### Update it -> version increments to 1, 2, 3...
PUT {{host}}/api/products/PUT_ID_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{ "price": 34.90, "stock": 38 }

### See the raw stored document (confirms the version field exists)
GET {{host}}/api/products/PUT_ID_HERE/raw


############################################################
# 2. Optimistic locking
############################################################

### Two writers race on the same version -> writerB hits OPTIMISTIC_LOCK_FAILURE
POST {{host}}/api/experiments/PUT_ID_HERE/concurrent-update


############################################################
# 3. Migration path: adding @Version to data that predates it
############################################################

### 3a. Create a LEGACY document with no version field (copy the returned id)
POST {{host}}/api/experiments/legacy-doc?name=Legacy%20Widget&category=misc&price=5.00&stock=10

### 3b. Confirm it has no version field
GET {{host}}/api/products/PUT_LEGACY_ID_HERE/raw

### 3c. Load-then-save the legacy doc -> FAILS with a duplicate-key error
###     (null version makes Spring Data think it is a new entity -> insert -> dup _id)
POST {{host}}/api/experiments/PUT_LEGACY_ID_HERE/load-then-save

### 3d. Inspect how many docs are missing the version field
GET {{host}}/api/migrations/version-stats

### 3e. Run the bulk back-fill: set version=0 where the field is missing
POST {{host}}/api/migrations/backfill-version

### 3f. Now load-then-save the SAME legacy doc again -> SUCCEEDS, version -> 1
POST {{host}}/api/experiments/PUT_LEGACY_ID_HERE/load-then-save

### 3g. Confirm every doc now has a version value
GET {{host}}/api/migrations/version-stats


############################################################
# 4. Lower-level MongoTemplate operations (bypass @Version)
############################################################

### $inc stock directly (does NOT touch version -> no optimistic locking)
POST {{host}}/api/experiments/PUT_ID_HERE/inc-stock?delta=5

### $mul prices across a whole category
POST {{host}}/api/experiments/raise-prices?category=electronics&multiplier=1.10

### Aggregation: counts per category
GET {{host}}/api/experiments/count-by-category

### Criteria search
GET {{host}}/api/products/search?category=electronics&minPrice=20


############################################################
# 5. Start over
############################################################

### Drop the whole collection (restart the app to re-seed)
POST {{host}}/api/experiments/reset
